content:
Changes to the Cases and Case Feed Mobile App

Available in both Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, and in Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

For organizations with "Page Layouts for Case Feed Users" enabled, users see the standard case layout. Standard actions on Case Feed aren’t available but several duplicating actions are available. These can be added to the Salesforce Mobile and Lightning Experience Actions section of the case page layout.

STANDARD ACTION AVAILABLE IN SALESFORCE CLASSIC	EQUIVALENT ACTION FOR THE SALESFORCE MOBILE APP
Email	Send Email
Change Case Status	Update Case
Log a Call	Log a Call

The Portal action isn’t available.

There are differences in behavior when using case Send Email actions:
- CC and BCC fields aren’t collapsible.
- HTML isn’t supported.
- Attachments can’t be included.
- Default email templates ignore attachments.
- Email drafts aren’t supported on the mobile app.
- Case comments can be created but not edited or deleted. The Case Comments related list doesn’t display full text of comments added on desktop sites.

Available case related lists on mobile apps:
- Case Contact Role
- Team Member List
- Team Member on Team List
- Team Template Member List

Not available case related lists on mobile apps:
- Business Hours on Holiday List
- Solution List
title: Changes to Cases and Case Feed Mobile App
